    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER - INSTALL - MAINSHAFT AND COUNTERSHAFTS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="7">
        <title>MAINSHAFT AND COUNTERSHAFTS</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift the assembly from the stand (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302376">Figure 76</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302376" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302376" filename="../figg13/G1302376.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 76. Mainshaft and Countershaft Installation</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>When moving heavy parts, use a chain hoist to help prevent personal injury.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 2nd-3rd shift fork (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302377">Figure 77</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302377" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302377" filename="../figg13/G1302377.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 77. Install 2nd - 3rd Shift Fork</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 1st-reverse shift fork (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302378">Figure 78</hotlnk>). Push the fork rails together.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302378" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302378" filename="../figg13/G1302378.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 78. Install 1st - Reverse Shift Fork</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure the 5th speed gear timing marks are aligned with the countershaft bores (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302379">Figure 79</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302379" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302379" filename="../figg13/G1302379.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 79. 5th Speed Gear Timing Marks Aligned</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the assembly in the clutch housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302380">Figure 80</hotlnk>). Make sure the 4th-5th speed fork shoes stay in place. A
                dab of light grease on the fork shoes will help them stay in place.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302380" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302380" filename="../figg13/G1302380.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 80. Assembly in Clutch Housing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply purple Loctite 515 or the equivalent to the clean housing face (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302381">Figure 81</hotlnk>). Then lower the main case into position, making sure the
                forks are aligned with the shift bar support bracket in the case.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302381" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302381" filename="../figg13/G1302381.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 81. Apply Loctite to Housing Face</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>When moving heavy parts, use a chain hoist to help prevent personal injury.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the case bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302382">Figure 82</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302382" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302382" filename="../figg13/G1302382.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 82. Install Case Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Do not overtighten the bolts; doing so could break the unit housing and flying parts could
                        cause personal injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <para>Tighten the bolts to 78 to 98 ft-lbs. (106 to 133 N&#8226;m).</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
